Mr. Kamthorn, head of the Math Department,

272
00:18:14,560 --> 00:18:17,400
is transferring to a new school next semester.

273
00:18:19,950 --> 00:18:21,230
What does that mean?

274
00:18:21,510 --> 00:18:25,890
It means it's time for you
to move out of the storage room.

275
00:18:27,040 --> 00:18:30,990
Congratulations on your
new desk in the Math Department.

276
00:18:33,430 --> 00:18:34,300
Really?

277
00:18:34,650 --> 00:18:35,820
This feels like a dream.

278
00:18:35,850 --> 00:18:37,820
I’ve waited two and a half years for this.

279
00:18:38,060 --> 00:18:41,540
I thought I’d have to wait until my next life.

280
00:18:49,420 --> 00:18:50,460
So…

281
00:18:51,030 --> 00:18:53,890
who’s the new head of department?

282
00:18:55,100 --> 00:18:58,360
Didn’t you get
what the principal just said, Mr. Tan?

283
00:18:59,670 --> 00:19:04,640
The desk you’re getting is
the head of the Math Department’s desk.

284
00:19:05,680 --> 00:19:06,490
What?!

285
00:19:08,240 --> 00:19:11,190
Congratulations, Mr. Tan!

286
00:19:18,490 --> 00:19:21,000
Everyone, please stop for a moment.

287
00:19:26,820 --> 00:19:32,440
Why am I the new head of department, sir?

288
00:19:33,700 --> 00:19:35,850
I-I mean, I’m still young.

289
00:19:36,250 --> 00:19:40,970
Oh dear. I didn’t prepare a script for this part.

290
00:19:42,050 --> 00:19:48,600
The principal believes you’re capable
and a representative of the new generation.

291
00:19:48,640 --> 00:19:55,620
With these qualities, we believe
you can help move the school forward.

292
00:19:55,810 --> 00:19:59,670
Plus, it’s great for PR.

293
00:19:59,700 --> 00:20:04,550
Should we post that you’re the youngest department head in school history?

294
00:20:18,710 --> 00:20:24,810
Thank you very much, sir, for considering me.

295
00:20:25,320 --> 00:20:29,190
But I’m truly happy being a regular teacher.

296
00:20:29,210 --> 00:20:30,750
I’m not ready for a promotion just yet.

297
00:20:34,880 --> 00:20:35,850
Ah.

298
00:20:37,750 --> 00:20:40,110
Well, if you insist.

299
00:20:47,050 --> 00:20:52,300
Do I still get a desk in the math department?

300
00:21:21,020 --> 00:21:22,360
When you’re ready, let me know.

301
00:21:22,390 --> 00:21:23,270
So we can talk.

302
00:21:31,270 --> 00:21:33,270
Do you want me to take the position?

303
00:21:36,450 --> 00:21:39,250
Whether I do or don’t isn’t relevant.

304
00:21:40,130 --> 00:21:43,550
I just don’t understand why
you turned down the opportunity.

305
00:21:51,990 --> 00:21:53,100
I don’t know.

306
00:21:54,040 --> 00:21:58,220
A promotion means more responsibility

307
00:21:58,860 --> 00:22:00,310
and more stress.

308
00:22:01,150 --> 00:22:02,880
Will I be happy?

309
00:22:04,680 --> 00:22:07,590
Are you happy staying in this room?

310
00:22:22,120 --> 00:22:23,690
Yeah, I am.

311
00:22:24,370 --> 00:22:27,770
That’s because of me, not the room.

312
00:22:29,590 --> 00:22:30,300
Right?

313
00:22:35,440 --> 00:22:36,160
Mm.

314
00:22:37,990 --> 00:22:39,150
You’re right.

315
00:22:42,700 --> 00:22:43,450
But still...

316
00:22:44,540 --> 00:22:51,210
Can’t I just be a regular teacher and
have a decent office at the same time?

317
00:22:53,900 --> 00:22:55,700
Do I really have to accept the promotion,

318
00:22:56,460 --> 00:22:57,870
take on more,

319
00:22:59,670 --> 00:23:03,080
just to get out of this dump?

320
00:23:08,950 --> 00:23:10,660
Don’t I have any other way?

321
00:23:47,350 --> 00:23:48,390
I understand.

322
00:24:01,750 --> 00:24:03,090
Come on down.

323
00:24:05,910 --> 00:24:06,980
You’re dead.

324
00:24:09,370 --> 00:24:13,160
So, how’s the US art college
application coming along?

325
00:24:13,410 --> 00:24:15,240
I think Kale applied for me.

326
00:24:16,490 --> 00:24:17,720
Do you have to take a test?

327
00:24:18,200 --> 00:24:19,430
Not sure.

328
00:24:19,670 --> 00:24:21,640
I heard it’s mostly
a portfolio submission and an interview.

329
00:24:24,190 --> 00:24:25,770
When’s the interview?

330
00:24:25,800 --> 00:24:27,120
Do you have to fly over there?

331
00:24:27,180 --> 00:24:28,340
I don’t know.

332
00:24:29,190 --> 00:24:30,080
Gosh!

333
00:24:32,790 --> 00:24:34,190
I got killed.

334
00:24:37,880 --> 00:24:39,270
Hey, Kim.

335
00:24:40,930 --> 00:24:42,060
Are you done exploring?

336
00:24:42,390 --> 00:24:45,050
Yeah. We went to every faculty.

337
00:24:45,090 --> 00:24:47,420
That’s enough. It’s exhausting.

338
00:24:48,330 --> 00:24:51,230
Want something to drink? I can get it for you.

339
00:24:51,530 --> 00:24:53,130
It’s okay, you get yours.

340
00:24:53,160 --> 00:24:53,960
Okay.

341
00:24:57,040 --> 00:24:59,040
Where are Per and Tar?

342
00:24:59,370 --> 00:25:01,870
Per said he’s helping out on a short film.

343
00:25:02,610 --> 00:25:05,540
Tar hasn’t replied to my messages yet.

344
00:25:05,560 --> 00:25:07,130
But I think they’re together.

345
00:25:07,520 --> 00:25:09,550
So, are they enrolling in Comm Arts together?

346
00:25:09,590 --> 00:25:10,900
For Tar, yes.

347
00:25:10,920 --> 00:25:12,810
But Per? I’m not sure.

348
00:25:13,260 --> 00:25:16,240
He said he didn’t want to
study Sports Science, though.

349
00:25:17,770 --> 00:25:20,650
Good. At least they’re clear.

350
00:25:21,430 --> 00:25:23,220
One knows what he wants,

351
00:25:23,240 --> 00:25:25,220
and the other knows what he doesn’t want.

352
00:25:31,190 --> 00:25:32,570
I’m worried about Kim.

353
00:25:33,450 --> 00:25:35,880
Even now, he still doesn’t know
what he wants to study.

354
00:25:38,200 --> 00:25:39,290
You mean Kim?

355
00:25:40,200 --> 00:25:41,470
That’s right.

356
00:25:42,100 --> 00:25:44,680
I took him to every faculty today,

357
00:25:44,970 --> 00:25:48,250
but… he didn’t seem to care.

358
00:26:02,630 --> 00:26:06,470
Kim passed the direct entrance exam
for Engineering at a university in Chiang Mai.

359
00:26:09,550 --> 00:26:11,640
He even said he wanted to go there.

360
00:26:20,340 --> 00:26:21,880
He didn’t tell you?

361
00:26:23,640 --> 00:26:24,360
No.

362
00:26:32,600 --> 00:26:34,120
Here’s your drink.

363
00:26:38,360 --> 00:26:39,370
What are you guys talking about?

364
00:26:43,800 --> 00:26:47,450
Kit, I think I’ll go check out
some more faculties.

365
00:26:47,880 --> 00:26:50,290
Should we head out before the event ends?

366
00:26:52,100 --> 00:26:53,910
Aren’t you enrolling in the Faculty of Science?

367
00:27:01,160 --> 00:27:02,120
Fine. I’m going too.

368
00:27:10,000 --> 00:27:11,580
Do you think they’ll fight?

369
00:27:15,170 --> 00:27:16,840
Let them fight.

370
00:27:17,240 --> 00:27:19,060
Maybe it’ll help clear the air.

371
00:27:20,380 --> 00:27:21,880
You mean them, right?

372
00:27:28,450 --> 00:27:32,200
So, what are you going to do
about the art college application?

373
00:27:34,430 --> 00:27:37,500
What-what do you mean?

374
00:27:38,740 --> 00:27:40,740
Can you be serious for once?

375
00:27:41,270 --> 00:27:44,280
You say “I don’t know” every time I ask.

376
00:27:44,630 --> 00:27:45,570
Why?

377
00:27:50,050 --> 00:27:52,050
Why do you have to be this serious?

378
00:27:57,110 --> 00:27:57,990
Okay.

379
00:27:59,210 --> 00:28:01,810
Kale sent me the application two days ago.

380
00:28:02,860 --> 00:28:03,910
No test required.

381
00:28:05,050 --> 00:28:07,720
Just submit my transcript
and do an online interview.

382
00:28:11,150 --> 00:28:13,850
Why didn’t you tell me that earlier?

383
00:28:15,910 --> 00:28:17,880
Why let me get all worked up first?

384
00:28:18,660 --> 00:28:20,690
Because I still don’t know if I should go.

385
00:28:22,310 --> 00:28:25,270
Why not decide after you get accepted?

386
00:28:27,470 --> 00:28:28,920
What if I do get in?

387
00:28:31,170 --> 00:28:33,170
It’s not that hard to get accepted.

388
00:28:34,210 --> 00:28:36,270
Kale wants me to study there first

389
00:28:36,810 --> 00:28:40,440
to build my portfolio
and then apply to bigger universities.

390
00:28:44,760 --> 00:28:46,480
Don’t you want to go?

391
00:28:53,040 --> 00:28:54,200
I do.

392
00:28:56,630 --> 00:28:57,510
But…

393
00:28:58,230 --> 00:29:00,230
I’m not sure if I should.

394
00:29:02,920 --> 00:29:04,470
I’ve never been far from home.

395
00:29:07,610 --> 00:29:10,930
I’ve never really accomplished anything.

396
00:29:11,810 --> 00:29:13,660
My English isn’t good enough.

397
00:29:15,410 --> 00:29:19,820
What if I don’t get into any university?

398
00:29:22,680 --> 00:29:24,470
Will I be hanging there without purpose?

399
00:29:30,360 --> 00:29:36,590
And what about us?

400
00:29:59,880 --> 00:30:02,280
Don’t jump too far ahead.

401
00:30:04,430 --> 00:30:07,720
When taking exams, you’re supposed
to tackle one problem at a time.

402
00:30:08,950 --> 00:30:10,950
You can’t solve everything at once.

403
00:30:14,030 --> 00:30:17,750
Right now, focus on the application first.

404
00:30:18,650 --> 00:30:21,280
After that, we’ll take it as it comes.

405
00:30:42,510 --> 00:30:43,350
Mm.

406
00:31:05,190 --> 00:31:07,430
Why didn’t you tell me you got accepted?

407
00:31:12,880 --> 00:31:15,530
You said we’d talk things out directly.

408
00:31:15,890 --> 00:31:17,520
I didn’t know how to tell you

409
00:31:17,560 --> 00:31:20,890
that we’d be studying at different universities, living in different towns.

410
00:31:22,430 --> 00:31:23,750
You didn’t know how to tell me,

411
00:31:23,790 --> 00:31:25,480
so you decided to lie?

412
00:31:33,590 --> 00:31:34,700
I’m sorry.

413
00:32:32,150 --> 00:32:34,320
Hey, you’re back early.

414
00:32:34,360 --> 00:32:35,870
You said you’d be home late.

415
00:32:50,790 --> 00:32:52,060
What’s wrong?

416
00:32:56,360 --> 00:32:58,890
Kim got accepted into the Faculty of Engineering at a university in Chiang Mai.

417
00:33:01,820 --> 00:33:03,290
But he didn’t tell me.

418
00:33:08,550 --> 00:33:09,610
It feels like...

419
00:33:11,890 --> 00:33:13,890
he’s planning a future

420
00:33:18,170 --> 00:33:20,170
that doesn’t have to include me.

421
00:33:33,750 --> 00:33:35,230
It’s okay, baby.

422
00:34:20,120 --> 00:34:22,900
CTU COMM ARTS

423
00:34:32,900 --> 00:34:34,550
I thought you left.

424
00:34:35,810 --> 00:34:37,090
Why would I leave early?

425
00:34:37,400 --> 00:34:39,030
It’s my faculty.

426
00:34:39,690 --> 00:34:42,429
You’re the one who
should study somewhere else.

427
00:34:42,960 --> 00:34:43,719
No.

428
00:34:44,480 --> 00:34:46,570
I just helped the seniors with their short film.

429
00:34:47,270 --> 00:34:49,100
And now, I know what I want.

430
00:34:50,170 --> 00:34:51,480
I’m going to study here too.

431
00:34:53,350 --> 00:34:56,179
They just used you for free, you know?

432
00:34:56,880 --> 00:34:59,200
At least I figured out what I want.

433
00:34:59,800 --> 00:35:02,410
You don’t even know
what you want from this faculty.

434
00:35:14,030 --> 00:35:15,210
Was that too harsh?

435
00:35:19,210 --> 00:35:21,870
No. You’re right.

436
00:35:26,860 --> 00:35:29,090
Honestly, I want to study here

437
00:35:29,630 --> 00:35:32,310
because a lot of famous people
graduated from this place.

438
00:35:33,690 --> 00:35:37,280
So I thought, maybe if I study here too,

439
00:35:38,870 --> 00:35:40,710
I’ll become famous someday.

440
00:35:44,170 --> 00:35:49,860
Do you think it’s silly
to choose something for that reason?

441
00:35:52,280 --> 00:35:53,050
No.

442
00:35:53,790 --> 00:35:57,370
By your standards, I don’t think it’s silly.

443
00:35:58,320 --> 00:36:00,010
Is that a compliment or an insult?

444
00:36:04,440 --> 00:36:10,120
I believe you’ll be famous one day.

445
00:36:11,380 --> 00:36:12,460
I don’t know why.

446
00:36:12,490 --> 00:36:13,670
It’s just a gut feeling.

447
00:36:22,250 --> 00:36:25,160
So... you’re really done with running?

448
00:36:26,030 --> 00:36:26,750
Mm.

449
00:36:29,220 --> 00:36:32,200
I started running when I was a kid
because I wasn’t good at school.

450
00:36:33,050 --> 00:36:34,440
So I became a runner.

451
00:36:34,710 --> 00:36:36,880
I was pretty good at it, so I stuck with it.

452
00:36:37,940 --> 00:36:41,290
But now, I want to
choose something I truly like.

453
00:36:43,510 --> 00:36:44,880
And you’ve found it.

454
00:36:47,370 --> 00:36:48,250
Yeah.

455
00:36:50,250 --> 00:36:51,960
Being a slate boy on set.

456
00:36:53,880 --> 00:36:56,440
You’re not picking Comm Arts
just to hold a slate.

457
00:37:00,850 --> 00:37:01,810
I know.

458
00:37:03,630 --> 00:37:05,870
You’re the one who wrote
that article in the yearbook.

459
00:37:09,150 --> 00:37:10,310
It was good.

460
00:37:26,210 --> 00:37:27,610
Do you think like me?

461
00:37:32,870 --> 00:37:35,000
I believe we just live our lives,

462
00:37:37,000 --> 00:37:39,750
and the future will shape what’s right for us.

463
00:37:54,760 --> 00:37:56,340
What are you even talking about?

464
00:37:56,890 --> 00:37:59,410
being a writer, are you turning poetic?

465
00:37:59,440 --> 00:38:00,170
Jerk!

466
00:38:01,800 --> 00:38:02,640
Damn you.

467
00:38:28,340 --> 00:38:30,730
I was right not to take
the department head position.

468
00:38:31,070 --> 00:38:33,610
I’d have so many
extra responsibilities after teaching.

469
00:38:33,650 --> 00:38:36,890
The life I want is one
with real work-life balance,

470
00:38:36,920 --> 00:38:40,730
where I can eat at my favorite place
with my boyfriend and join an activity or two.

471
00:38:40,760 --> 00:38:43,100
Hey, I’m thinking about taking yoga classes.

472
00:38:45,560 --> 00:38:46,920
Yoga? You?

473
00:38:47,440 --> 00:38:50,380
Mm. Most people with free time do yoga.

474
00:38:50,930 --> 00:38:54,160
Hey, should I try rock climbing too?

475
00:38:54,870 --> 00:38:59,450
Let’s just say, I’m not spending
most of my time working.

476
00:38:59,910 --> 00:39:01,510
It’s good you think that way.

477
00:39:01,550 --> 00:39:03,200
That means we’ll have more time together.

478
00:39:11,090 --> 00:39:13,480
Seriously, though.

479
00:39:13,520 --> 00:39:15,180
Being the head doesn’t guarantee success.

480
00:39:15,240 --> 00:39:19,350
Sometimes, you just get more responsibility and still get ignored by your boss.

481
00:39:19,370 --> 00:39:22,310
traps disguised as success.
High positions are just

482
00:39:22,590 --> 00:39:25,100
Meanwhile, lower positions
let you live happier.

483
00:39:30,710 --> 00:39:33,160
You actually want
the department head role, don’t you?

484
00:39:36,850 --> 00:39:40,240
And now, you regret turning it down.

485
00:39:42,180 --> 00:39:43,050
Ridiculous!

486
00:39:43,950 --> 00:39:45,230
What are you talking about?

487
00:39:53,020 --> 00:39:53,860
Yes.

488
00:39:55,490 --> 00:39:58,700
At first, I thought I was right.

489
00:39:59,550 --> 00:40:01,730
But it still bothers me until now.

490
00:40:11,080 --> 00:40:12,570
The truth is, I was scared.

491
00:40:16,470 --> 00:40:21,680
Scared I wouldn’t live up to
people’s expectations.

492
00:40:23,070 --> 00:40:27,900
Scared that once I took the job,

493
00:40:29,010 --> 00:40:31,260
I’d realize I didn’t deserve it.

494
00:40:36,720 --> 00:40:37,880
Or…

495
00:40:38,520 --> 00:40:41,880
maybe you’d find out that you’re doing great.

496
00:40:44,520 --> 00:40:46,780
Don’t assume the future will be disappointing.

497
00:40:49,500 --> 00:40:53,410
There must be a reason
the principal believes in you.

498
00:40:54,090 --> 00:40:58,790
Now you just need to believe in yourself.

499
00:41:05,760 --> 00:41:07,760
And if you ever need emotional support,

500
00:41:08,360 --> 00:41:09,720
I’m always here.

501
00:41:19,940 --> 00:41:23,850
Okay. I’ll call the principal now.

502
00:41:28,270 --> 00:41:30,030
Should I call now or wait till tomorrow?

503
00:41:30,070 --> 00:41:32,540
You can call him now. It’s just 7.

504
00:41:37,600 --> 00:41:38,970
I’m pressing the call button now!

505
00:41:56,890 --> 00:41:57,630
Mon.

506
00:42:09,330 --> 00:42:14,040
I’m sorry for not telling you I got accepted.

507
00:42:17,480 --> 00:42:22,540
I already knew my scores weren’t enough
to get into the same university as you.

508
00:42:24,300 --> 00:42:26,440
Engineering there requires such a high score.

509
00:42:27,770 --> 00:42:29,850
So when I got into
that university in Chiang Mai,

510
00:42:33,200 --> 00:42:36,960
I felt like I didn’t have the right to turn it down.

511
00:42:40,050 --> 00:42:41,500
If I hadn’t found out myself,

512
00:42:42,540 --> 00:42:44,280
when were you planning to tell me?

513
00:42:46,280 --> 00:42:51,440
To be honest, I don’t know.

514
00:42:54,490 --> 00:42:55,880
I was scared to tell you.

515
00:42:58,170 --> 00:43:00,170
I was afraid you’d break up with me.

516
00:43:02,810 --> 00:43:03,880
So this whole time,

517
00:43:04,960 --> 00:43:06,350
you’ve been carrying that fear?

518
00:43:10,770 --> 00:43:14,520
I was scared you’d want to
end things because we’d be far apart.

519
00:43:22,290 --> 00:43:23,190
Okay.

520
00:43:24,150 --> 00:43:26,510
I know I shouldn’t have kept it from you.

521
00:43:32,360 --> 00:43:37,340
So if you want to break up, I’ll accept it.

522
00:43:46,510 --> 00:43:47,340
Why?

523
00:43:48,540 --> 00:43:51,020
Do you think I’m that fickle?

524
00:43:53,210 --> 00:43:54,730
It’s just distance.

525
00:43:55,670 --> 00:43:57,780
You think that’s enough to make me give up?

526
00:44:09,000 --> 00:44:10,340
Does that mean…

527
00:44:12,910 --> 00:44:14,650
it’s not a problem

528
00:44:16,150 --> 00:44:17,690
if we go to different universities?

529
00:44:27,080 --> 00:44:30,480
If you’re okay with it, then I am too.

530
00:45:15,880 --> 00:45:20,020
SCHOOL’S OUT COUNTDOWN

531
00:45:20,070 --> 00:45:21,810
DON’T WANT TO LEAVE MY BUDS YET!
FINGERS CROSSED CU ACCEPTS ME!
SKIPPED CLASSES
AND STILL MADE IT TO GRADUATION!

532
00:45:21,830 --> 00:45:24,490
THANK YOU FOR MAKING MY HIGH SCHOOL LIFE MEANINGFUL AND MEMORABLE.

533
00:45:53,310 --> 00:45:54,070
Shane.

